# Privacy Policy – Simple Mermaid Preview

**Last updated: March 13, 2026**

## Overview

Simple Mermaid Preview is a Chrome extension that detects and renders Mermaid diagram code blocks on web pages. We are committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains what data (if any) is collected and how it is used.

## Data We Do Not Collect

This extension does **not** collect, transmit, store on any server, or share:

- Personally identifiable information
- Browsing history or visited URLs
- Page content or diagram content
- Any analytics or usage data

## Local Storage

The extension uses Chrome's `storage` API solely to save your personal preferences (such as theme settings) **locally on your device**. This data never leaves your browser and is never transmitted anywhere.

## Permissions Explained

- **activeTab** – Used to communicate between the popup and the current tab when you click the extension icon.
- **storage** – Used to persist your preferences locally on your device.
- **Content scripts on all URLs** – Required to detect and render Mermaid code blocks on any webpage you visit, including AI chat interfaces like ChatGPT and Claude.

## Third Parties

We do not share, sell, or transfer any user data to third parties. All processing happens entirely within your browser.

## Changes to This Policy

If this policy changes, the updated version will be published at this URL with a revised "Last updated" date.

## Contact

If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please open an issue on the extension's GitHub repository.
